            <div class = 'newsEntry'>
            <h3><a href = 'http://martinfowler.com/snips/201011240526.html'>Electronic copies of the DSL book</a></h3>
            
            <p class = 'date'>Wed 24 Nov 2010 05:26</p>
            
            <div class = 'content'><p>Here&#8217;s an update on the electronic versions of my <a href='http://martinfowler.com/books.html#dsl'>DSL book</a>.</p>
            
            <ul>
            <li>Amazon has a kindle version available</li>
            
            <li>InformtIT has a epub/pdf bundle</li>
            
            <li>Apple has epub in the ibookstore</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p>I keep the links to these sources on the <a href='http://martinfowler.com/books.html#dsl'>dsl book page</a></p>
            
            <p>At this point I&#8217;m not too happy with the cross references, which aren&#8217;t hot linked. We&#8217;re working on fixing that. Ebook workflows are still new and an edge case for mainline publications like Pearson, but we&#8217;re working to shake up the production chain and make it a bit more this-millennium.</p></div>
            </div>
